# CompanyScope API contract rules

## General contract expectations
- Keep APIs RESTful and predictable
- Use explicit versioning if breaking changes are introduced
- Validate all request parameters
- Return structured error objects
- Do not leak internal-only fields unless explicitly intended

## Core endpoint groups
- search
- company aggregate
- filings
- financials
- signals
- officers
- ownership / PSC
- charges
- watchlists
- internal ingestion endpoints

## Response design rules
- Include `last_refreshed_at` where freshness matters
- Include `source` or provenance metadata where relevant
- Include confidence metadata for parsed facts and derived metrics
- Separate unavailable values from zero values
- Use pagination for filing lists and large collections

## Error format
Every error response should include:
- error code
- human-readable message
- optional details
- retryable boolean where helpful

## Contract discipline
- If a frontend shape changes, update the API spec
- If a parser output shape changes, update downstream schemas
- Avoid mixing raw upstream fields and product-normalised fields without clear naming
- Prefer stable field names over mirroring noisy upstream naming
